The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, November 04, 2002 				 Forensic tests and decibel devils 
								Balaram Bardhan: Which crackers are banned? Suppose a person does burst a banned cracker, how can he be identified and punished?																																																													The nomenclature is not the factor. It should be seen whether the cracker crosses the decibel limit. It is difficult to nab a culprit on the spot. But the cracker can be identified and sent for a forensic test to check for the decibel limit. And proper evidence needs to be collected to locate the person.
